    "body": "#Kaldi is a toolkit for speech recognition written in C++ and licensed under the Apache License v2.0. Kaldi is intended for use by speech recognition researchers. It has quite a number of dependency packages. This PR hosts a board for watching progress on building Kaldi.\r\n\r\nThe following list may keep increasing as I build kaldi.\r\n\r\n- [x] sctk (#3325 merged)\r\n- [x] openfst (#3324 merged)\r\n- [x] sph2pipe\r\n- [x] speedx\r\n- [x] kaldi CPU version\r\n- [x] kaldi GPU verison\r\n\r\n- [x] Add `# Does not use Aututools` to kaldi\r\n- [x] Refine the BLAS configuration (check `petsc` and `trillioins`) \r\n- [x] Substitute `find` with `os.walk()`.\r\n- [x] Substitute `rsync` with `os.walk()`.\r\n- [x] Patch `sph2pipe` with a CMake file.",
